l movie \"Thambikku Entha Ooru\" sung by SPB.\n\n==Critical reception==\n''Sadma'' received widespread critical acclaim with major appreciation drawn towards Sridevi's performance. On [[IMDb]], the film has a high score of 8.5/10.\nIt is included in iDiva's list of '10 Must Watch Movies That Weren't Blockbusters'.<ref name=\"idiva.com\">{{cite web|last=idiva.com|title=10 Must Watch Movies That Weren't Blockbusters|url=http://idiva.com/photogallery-entertainment/10-mustwatch-movies-that-werent-blockbusters/6659}}</ref> Sridevi's performance as a child-woman suffering from amnesia was called by  [[Indian Express]] \"''a milestone in her illustrious career\"''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Indian Express|title=The Forbidden Love|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/the-forbidden-love/961045}}</ref> Sridevi also featured in the [[Mid Day]] list of  'Challenging Roles played by Bollywood Actors' describing her act in the film as \"''her best performance ever\"''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Mid-day|title=Challenging Roles played by Bollywood actors|url=http://www.mid-day.com/photos/b-town-specials/challenging-roles-played-by-bollywood-actors/}}</ref> In 2012, [[Adil Hussain]], Sridevi's co-star in ''[[English Vinglish]]'' revealed that he became a fan of the actress after watching her in ''Sadma''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Bollywoodtrade.com|title=Adil Hussain: I became Sridevi's fan after watching SADMA |url=http://www.bollywoodtrade.com/trade-news/adil-hussain-i-became-sridevis-fan-after-watching-sadma-/index.htm}}</ref> The Sridevi-Kamal Haasan pair also appeared on the [[CNN-IBN]] list of 'Greatest Romantic Couples on Celluloid'.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=CNN-IBN|title=100 Years of Indian Cinema: The greatest romantic couples on celluloid|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/photogallery/12608.html}}</ref> The climax of ''Sadma'' is included in the [[CNN-IBN]] list of 'Bollywood's 50 Most Memorable Scenes of All Time'.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=CNN-IBN|title=100 Years of Indian Cinema: Bollywood's 50 most memorable scenes of all time|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/photogallery/13323-24.html}}</ref>\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n\n===Filmfare Awards===\n;Nominated\n*[[Filmfare Award for Best Story]] - [[Balu Mahendra]]\n*[[Filmfare Best Actor Award]] - [[Kamal Haasan]]\n*[[Filmfare Best Actress Award]] - [[Sridevi Kapoor]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|0086230|Sadma}}\n* {{rotten-tomatoes|id=Sadma|title=Sadma}} \n\n{{Balu Mahendra}}\n\n[[Category:1980s Hindi-language films]]\n[[Category:1983 films]]\n[[Category:Hindi remakes of Tamil films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Balu Mahendra]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Ooty]]\n[[Category:Hindi film scores by Ilaiyaraaja]]\n[[Category:Films about amnesia]]\n", "name_user": "TMProofreader", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sadma"}
